{
    "word": "Tribulation",
    "definitions": [
        "That which occasions distress, trouble, or vexation; severe affliction."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "When tribulation or persecution ariseth because of the word, by and by he is offended.",
        "In the world ye shall have tribulation."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. tribulacium, F. tribulation, L. tribulatio, from tribulare to press, afflict, fr. tribulum a thrashing sledge, akin to terere, tritum, to rub. See Trite.]"
}